\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces Fee-dependent security inversion. CTV fee pinning (blue) executes in one block regardless of fee rate. CCV per-UTXO recovery-cost scaling (red) requires progressively fewer blocks as fees rise, because each split creates a larger dust threshold. Below ${\sim }50$~sat/vB, exhaustion requires hundreds of blocks (infeasible). Above $r^* \approx 66$~sat/vB, exhaustion completes within a few blocks, making it practical. The crossover defines where the safety ranking inverts.}}{59}{figure.caption.43}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:fee_inversion}{{5.1}{59}{Fee-dependent security inversion. CTV fee pinning (blue) executes in one block regardless of fee rate. CCV per-UTXO recovery-cost scaling (red) requires progressively fewer blocks as fees rise, because each split creates a larger dust threshold. Below ${\sim }50$~sat/vB, exhaustion requires hundreds of blocks (infeasible). Above $r^* \approx 66$~sat/vB, exhaustion completes within a few blocks, making it practical. The crossover defines where the safety ranking inverts}{figure.caption.43}{}}
