\newlabel{fig:recovery_griefing}{{5.4}{66}{Recovery griefing loop (\textbf {TM2}) for CCV. The attacker triggers permissionless recovery (122\vB {}); the owner must re-deposit and re-trigger (454\vB {}) to resume withdrawal; the attacker invokes recovery again. The per-round cost asymmetry $\gamma = 0.27$ strongly favors the attacker}{figure.caption.50}{}}
