\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.5}{\ignorespaces Trigger key theft race (\textbf  {TM3}). The attacker broadcasts an unvault (upper lane). The watchtower detects it at time $\delta $ and broadcasts recovery (lower lane). The outcome hinges on whether recovery confirms before CSV expiry: safe if recovery wins, DoS if tied, theft if the attacker successfully pins the watchtower's transaction (combining TM3 with TM1).}}{68}{figure.caption.52}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:trigger_theft}{{5.5}{68}{Trigger key theft race (\textbf {TM3}). The attacker broadcasts an unvault (upper lane). The watchtower detects it at time $\delta $ and broadcasts recovery (lower lane). The outcome hinges on whether recovery confirms before CSV expiry: safe if recovery wins, DoS if tied, theft if the attacker successfully pins the watchtower's transaction (combining TM3 with TM1)}{figure.caption.52}{}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {section}{\numberline {5.7}Class Z5{}: Cold-Key Theft via Unconstrained Recovery (TM11)}{68}{section.5.7}\protected@file@percent }
